msDesc.head: Acts and proceedings from the canonization process of St Birgitta of Sweden

supportDesc.foliation: Foliation 1-255 in pencil by a modern hand takes account of the two inserted leaves at the back.

p.note: Top of page in black ink by a modern hand: Kongl. Biblioteket Stockholm. Below in pencil: A. 14

Top of page in black ink: F I 4us. Middle of page in black ink by a contemporary hand: 4 folio references to mentions of Katarina. Lower right corner in black ink by a contemporary hand: 4 Latin words. Lower left corner in black ink: G.

binding.p: Binding from Vadstena(of an older type?). Brown leather over wooden boards. 4 double spinebands and 2 endbands. Pinclasps with anchorplates on and pins on . In lower left corner on LCO a green label: Hs-Bibliotheket, Stockholm. Handskrifter. Kyrkohistoria. Sv. Medeltid. At the top of RCO a shelfmark in black ink: F I. Centre of RCO in black ink on a parchment label, text partly worn off: Attestaciones b F I. Shelfmarks visible on the : 74; on a white label: A 14; in gold at the bottom: A 14
binding.condition: Leather torn and cracked along the spine where parts are missing, making endbands and upper bind visible. Nails near spine protruding through the cover. Wooden boards visible through holes. Straps for clasps lost with traces left in the anchorplates.

history.origin:
Written by Italian scribes c. 1391 in Rome , see Collijn (1924–1924)
.
history.provenance: Belonged to the library of Vadstenamonastery. Vadstena shelfmark F I 4us on the , F I on the and again on the title label, almost worn off.

To the Royal Chancery in 1620 and in the 1670s to the Antiquities Archive, see Collijn (1924–1924)
. The manuscript is listed in the archive inventories: in the 1722 catalogue U 90:4 as 74, shelfmark visible on the ; in U 91:2:1 as G 74, the letter G written on , and also as 14. The current signum is used for the first time in Helin's inventory U 91:2:2.
history.acquisition: From the Antiquities Archive to the National Library of Sweden in 1780.

msItem.title: Summary of the canonization process of St Birgitta of Sweden
msItem.rubric: Rubricacio seu summa. Rubricacio seu summa tocius processus canonizacionis beate Brigide de Swecia
msItem.incipit: In nomine yhesu christi Misericordis et pii Ac eius Virginis matris et Beati Ieronimi Amen. QVia dominus noster papa et Collegium Cardinalium multis et arduis que in Romane curie alueum vndique confluunt quasi torrens
msItem.explicit: ixl dies accedentibus uero singulis infra octauas dei festi ad sepulchrum ipsum. xl. dies de iniuncta sibi penitencia misericorditer Relaxamus.

note.p: The rubric is inscribed on in a tall, compressed and elaborate style. The upper parts of the letters in the word beate are missing due to a tear in the leaf.

supportDesc.foliation: Contemporary foliation in brown-black ink (by same scribe as some of the marginal notes?): i-xxi (). is blank without original foliation. Leaf numbering in red in the lower left corner of each verso in the form of letters a-r and numbers ii-xv starts on (a i was probably in the lower corner of but is now lost). Pagination running from a 4 to a 40 in pale lead point in the middle of the lower margin on . eorundem et in specie.
supportDesc.condition: lower quarter of leaf missing, no text loss. horizontal tear from the outer edge one quarter down on the page, ca 8 cm in length.

p.note: Top of the page in an early modern hand: 6
Top margin in black ink in a medieval hand: Acta et processus Canonizationis S. Birgittae de Suecia.
Marginal notes and manicules added on almost every page by the main hand and at least one other, contemporary hand.

decoDesc.p: Main text in brown-black ink. Some underlining in red on .
decoDesc.decoNote:
In the rubric a plain initial I over 2 lines in black ink with a face in profile in the counterspace. Opening initial Q in black ink with simple leaf decoration in bows and counter space.
Plain initials, E and C, in black ink extending above the line with simple leaf decoration in bow and counter space. Initial A over 2 lines with a man's face in the counter space.

msItem.title: Acts and proceedings from the canonization process of St Birgitta of Sweden
msItem.rubric: Acta et processus habitus coram Reuerendissimis in christo patribus dominis Gradensi Corphiensi et de zangro Cardinalibus Commissariis super negocio Canonizacionis Beate Brigide de Regno Swecie
msItem.incipit: In nomine domini Amen Anno a natiuitate eiusdem Millesimo Tricentesimo Septuagesimo nono. Indiccione secunda die Iouis tercio mensis marcij ponit sanctissimi in christo patris et domini nostri domini vrbani diuina prouidencia pape sexti Anno primo. In mei notarii publici et testium infrascriptorum presencia discretus vir Nereus Nerey Cursor et magister Cursorum domini nostri pape
msItem.explicit: vt predictorum copiam dicto sindico et procuratori et quibuscumque aliis eam petentibus et habere volentibus trademur predictorum petencium sumptibus et expensis.
msItem.note: Below final rubric is written: Incipiunt attestaciones testium productorum et receptorum in Roma super sancto Canonizacionis pie memorie domine Brigide de Regno Swecie. Continuando folium sequens et cetera.

msItem.title: Attestations from individual witnesses
msItem.rubric: Incipiunt deposiciones testium productorum et receptorum in Roma Super articulis et miraculis pie memorie domine Beate Brigide de Regno Swecie ac Super negocio canonisacionis ipsius et cetera.
msItem.incipit: In christi nomine Amen sequuntur attestaciones testium productorum super vita conuersacione et miraculis recolende memorie domine Brigide
msItem.explicit: Cetera vero signa et sigilla dictis scripturis appensa et consignata dixit ipse testis illis sibi exhibitis non cognoscere.
msItem.finalRubric: Et sic sit finis huiusmodi processus et cetera. laus christo et gloria per seculorum secula Amen.

msItem.title: Supplication letters for the canonization process of St Birgitta
msItem.rubric: littere supplicatorie pro Canonizacione beate Brigide.
msItem.incipit: Hic sequuntur tres littere Supplicatorie directe domino vrbano pape vi pro Canonizacione beate Brigide de quibus fit mencio supra folio xxiijj in margine hoc est Cxiiii. Sanctissimo in christo patri ac domino domino suo Carissimo domino vrbano
msItem.explicit: sic eciam ad placandam diuine maiestatis offensam suis sanctis precibus esse dignetur patrona misericors et favorabilis advocata. Datum Orabro Strengianensis diocesis Anno ab incarnacione Millesimo CCC Septuagesimo nono xviii die mensis Ianuarii sub Sigillis nostris.
msItem.note: The words hoc est Cxiiii are an addition to the incipit by another hand, after which a space of ca four lines has been left blank. Below last line of the explicit the phrase hoc est die prisce virginis is added.

supportDesc.foliation: Contemporary foliation in brown-black ink by a different hand (main scribe ?) i-clix () and clxx-ccxxix (). Numbers lxxxix-xcv () and ci-ciii () corrected. Numbers cl-clxix skipped and clxx erroneously corrected to clxi (?). Leaf numbering in red in the lower outer corner of the verso-side b vii-r xi (), often worn off. Reuerendis patribus
supportDesc.condition: bottom outer corners missing, no text loss. two lengthwise tears.

p.note:
Marginal notes, nota-signs and manicules passim. Running title and subtitles added in the top margin in a contemporary hand beginning on fol. 24r: Atestationes Deposicio domini cardinalis Theatini
.
Top outer corner in black ink in a contemporary hand: 6 chapter references. Middle of page in black ink in same hand and style as : processus canonizacionis beate brigide de swecia.

: Bookmarks in red leather sewn on to page.

msItem.title: Collection of miracles concerning St Birgitta
msItem.incipit: Margareta filia haraldi muratoris et uxoris eius cecilie de ciuitate stocholmiensi Vpsalensis [post corr. ex strengnensis] dyocesis ceca nata mansit in eadem cecitate per dimidium annum
msItem.explicit: statim surgentes exierunt per medias plateas et portas ciuitatis ita secure quod nullus eis verbum contrarium loqueretur Hi anno domini Mo ccc xco in ascensione domini ad monasterium watzstenense venientes hoc iuramento prestito ad [post corr. ex et] sancta ewangelia firma constancia asserebant.

p.note: This leaf is an insertion in the volume.

Bottom of page in black ink by early modern hand: Finis
.

msItem.title: Instruction from cardinal Lucas de Gentilibus concerning the examination of the miracles
msItem.rubric: Notabile qualiter et quomodo miracula sanctorum debeant examinari
msItem.incipit: Modus tenendus super eo quod queritur a me videtur michi quod debeat esse talis videlicet
msItem.explicit: et isti procuratores dicta miracula sic autentico modo conscripta Remittant ad dictum dominum episcopum et monasterium quolibet anno certo tempore.
